<br>
If the President said we have a prime suspect and we will now go after him, then fine, but that is NOT what the President says at the moment.<br>
<br>
Also, even if the prime suspect turns out to be PROVEN to be behind this, I think more importantly he was saying not to judge a nation or an ethnic group based on that.  The President will decide who should be punished, lets let him decide instead of pointing fingers.  If you want to say anyone who contributed to this is guilty, we can probably find a way to prove most people in this country were a contributing part of it just for paying their taxes.  I do not wish to get into that, just realize that many things we do affect the world.  Let the President decide who should be punished for this.  <br>
The same way you allow the judicial system to decide who should be punished.  Remember sometimes it can help an investigation to provide immunity to someone who has key information for a more important guilty party.  Not to say this will happen, but it might.<br>
<br>
I may not agree with everything Bush says or does, but I have put my trust in him to handle this appropriately.  If he does not, I have my vote next Election Day.<br>
<br>
God Bless America.  God Bless GWB.  God Bless this planet.<br>
